column3: while the Adaptive system relies on highly specific antigen receptors such as T-cell receptors (TCRs) and B-cell receptors (BCRs). The Innate system components include proteins like MyD88 and NF-κB
column4:
whereas the Adaptive system involves proteins such as RAG1/2 for V(D)J recombination and CD4+ helper T cells. These pathways show distinct molecular mechanisms in immune response initiation and specificity.
